    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is offset by the high relevance of the validation activity to the COU, the multi-laboratory experimental dataset, and the conservative acceptance bounds. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support regulatory use of the FEA model for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw compression-bending COU at medium assurance level.",
